= \n| membership_year = 2020\n| membership = {{increase}} 266,440<ref>{{cite web|title=\u0130yi Parti|url=https://www.yargitaycb.gov.tr/icerik/1338|website=Yarg\u0131tay Cumhuriyet Ba\u015fsavc\u0131l\u0131\u011f\u0131|publisher=Yarg\u0131tay|accessdate=15 February 2020|language=Turkish}}</ref>\n| position = {{Nowrap|[[Centrism|Centre]]<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2017/10/turkish-minister-meral-aksener-launches-party-171025200606462.html|title=Ex-Turkish minister Meral Aksener launches new party|first=Umut|last=Uras|date=25 October 2017|publisher=[[Al Jazeera English]]|quote=Meral Aksener, ex-interior minister, unveils centrist Good Party}}</ref><ref name=\"party program\">{{cite web|url=http://iyiparti.org.tr/Assets/pdf/iyi_parti_programi.pdf|title=\u0130yi Parti - Parti Program\u0131|date=25 October 2017|accessdate=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"hurriyet.com.tr\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/umit-ozdag-merkez-sag-degil-milli-merkez-40549074|title=\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f: Merkez sa\u011f de\u011fil, milli merkez|publisher=H\u00fcrriyet|date=13 August 2017}}</ref><ref name=euron>{{cite news|title=Turkey's Good Party emerges as serious challenger to Erdogan|url=http://www.euronews.com/2018/01/10/turkey-s-good-party-emerges-as-serious-challenger-to-erdogan|work=Euronews|date=10 January 2018}}</ref> to <br> [[Centre-right politics|centre-right]]<ref>[https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/nationalist-mp-forms-new-party-to-challenge-erdogan-fffwvh7vl Nationalist forms new party to challenge Erdogan]. ''The Sunday Times''. Author - Hannah Lucinda Smith. Published 25 October 2017. Retrieved 10 December 2017.</ref><ref>[https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2018/4/22/turkish-opposition-leader-says-erdogan-will-lose-election Turkish opposition leader says Erdogan will lose election]. ''The New Arab''. Published 22 April 2018. Retrieved 2 October 2018.</ref><ref>[http://www.epc.eu/documents/uploads/pub_8534_turkey_votes_-_snap_elections.pdf?doc_id=1988 Turkey votes. Snap elections  \u2013 Turkey at yet another crossroads]. ''European Policy Centre''. Published 15 May 2018. Retrieved 2 October 2018.</ref>}}\n| seats1_title = [[Grand National Assembly of Turkey|Grand National Assembly]]\n| seats1 = {{Composition bar|37|600|#42ABE2}}\n| seats2_title = [[Metropolitan municipalities in Turkey|Metropolitan<br />municipalities]]\n| seats2 = {{Composition bar|0|30|#42ABE2}}\n| seats3_title = [[List of municipalities in Turkey|District<br />municipalities]]\n| seats3 = {{Composition bar|24|1351|#42ABE2}}\n| seats5_title = [[2019 Turkish local elections|Provincial councillors]]\n| seats5 = {{Composition bar|23|1251|#42ABE2}}\n| colours = {{Color box|#42ABE2|border=darkgray}} [[Blue]] {{Color box|#fCD700|border=darkgray}} [[Yellow]]\n| seats6_title = [[2019 Turkish local elections|Municipal Assemblies]]\n| seats6 = {{Composition bar|1092|20498|#42ABE2}}\n| flag = [[File:Flag of the Good Party.svg|200px|border|Flag of the \u0130yi Party]]\n| website = {{url|http://iyiparti.org.tr}}\n| country = Turkey\n}}\n\nThe '''\u0130yi Party''' (translated into [[English language|English]] as '''The Good Party''')<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/aksener-hints-at-run-for-presidency-in-2019-as-she-forms-good-party-121370|title=Ak\u015fener hints at run for presidency in 2019 as she forms \u2018Good Party\u2019|website=H\u00fcrriyet Daily News|language=en|access-date=2018-04-25}}</ref> is a [[Turkish nationalism|nationalist]], [[Liberal conservatism|liberal-conservative]], [[Secularism|secularist]] [[List of political parties in Turkey|political party]] in [[Turkey]] which aims to overcome [[social justice|social injustice]] by forming a well functioning [[welfare state|social state]].<ref name=dw/><ref name=\"haberturk.com\"/><ref name=\"Welfare State\"/><ref name=\"party program\"/><ref name=\"social justice\"/> Established on 25 October 2017 by its current leader [[Meral Ak\u015fener]], the party adheres to the [[Kemalism|principles and ideals]] of Turkey's founder [[Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yenicaggazetesi.com.tr/iyi-parti-mustafa-kemal-ataturkun-huzurunda-175767h.htm|title=\u0130yi Parti Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk'\u00fcn huzurunda|publisher=}}</ref> Their [[fraternal party]] is the liberal conservative [[Democrat Party (Turkey, current)|Democrat Party]].<ref>http://www.yenicaggazetesi.com.tr/dpden-aksener-karari-191415h.htm</ref>\n\nIt follows a centrist political ideology and puts a particular emphasis on the restoration of the [[parliamentary system]] and the integrity of the judiciary and other institutions.<ref name=dw/><ref name=\"sozcu.com.tr\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sozcu.com.tr/2017/gundem/iyi-partinin-programindan-en-onemli-dis-dusman-feto-2062644/|title=\u0130Y\u0130 Parti\u2019nin program\u0131ndan fla\u015f detaylar: En \u00f6nemli i\u00e7 d\u00fc\u015fman\u2026|last=|first=|date=2017-10-25|website=[[S\u00f6zc\u00fc]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://onedio.com/haber/aksener-liderligindeki-iyi-parti-hedeflerini-siraladi-yeniden-parlamenter-sisteme-donulecek-792530|title=Ak\u015fener Liderli\u011findeki \u0130yi Parti, 15 Temel Hedefini S\u0131ralad\u0131: 'Yeniden Parlamenter Sisteme D\u00f6n\u00fclecek'|last=|first=|date=2017-10-25|website=Onedio.com|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The party has been widely described as an anti-[[Erdo\u011fanism|Erdo\u011fanist]] alternative for right-leaning voters disillusioned with both the [[Nationalist Movement Party]] (MHP) and the governing [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|Justice and Development Party]] (AKP).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sozcu.com.tr/2017/gundem/meral-aksener-kimdir-aksenerin-partisinin-adi-ne-oldu-iyi-partinin-acilimi-ne-olacak-2062395/|title=\u0130Y\u0130 Parti kuruluyor, a\u00e7\u0131l\u0131m\u0131 ne olacak? Meral Ak\u015fener kimdir? \u0130Y\u0130 Parti\u2019de kimler var?|last=|first=|date=25 October 2017|work=[[S\u00f6zc\u00fc]]|accessdate=25 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meral Ak\u015fener'in partisinin ad\u0131: \u0130yi Parti|url=http://www.posta.com.tr/meral-aksener-in-partisinin-adi-belli-oldu-iyi-parti-haberi-1345481|accessdate=25 October 2017|work=Posta|date=25 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Meral Ak\u015fener\u2019in \u0130Y\u0130 Partisi, T\u00fcrkiye\u2019nin faaliyetteki 87. partisi oluyor|url=http://halktv.com.tr/meral-aksenerin-iyi-partisi-turkiyenin-faaliyetteki-87-partisi-oluyor-240057|accessdate=25 October 2017|work=Halk TV|date=25 October 2017}}</ref> In addition to meaning 'good', the name \u0130yi is also inspired by the [[Kay\u0131 tribe]] flag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/meral-aksenerin-partisinin-ismi-kayi-boyundan-mi-esinlenildi-40622029|title=Meral Ak\u015fener'in partisinin ismi Kay\u0131 Boyu'ndan m\u0131 esinlenildi?|last=|first=|date=2017-10-25|website=[[H\u00fcrriyet]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe party was formed by prominent former members of Turkey's main established parties, most notably the MHP and the main opposition [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]] (CHP). Plans to form a new party emerged amongst prominent MHP defectors after the MHP's support for a 'Yes' vote in the controversial [[2017 Turkish constitutional referendum|2017 constitutional referendum]], as well as [[2016 Nationalist Movement Party Extraordinary Congress|a failed attempt]] to unseat the party's governing leader. In addition to endorsing a more moderate [[civic nationalism]] as opposed to the ardent [[ethnic nationalism]] of the MHP, the party runs on an [[Anti-establishmentarianism|anti-establishment]] platform criticising both the governing and opposition parties in Turkey for their ineffectiveness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/meral-aksener-biz-siyasi-yelpazede-bir-alan-doldurmak-icin-yola-cikmis-degiliz-40568540|title=Meral Ak\u015fener: Biz, siyasi yelpazede bir alan doldurmak i\u00e7in yola \u00e7\u0131km\u0131\u015f de\u011filiz|last=|first=|date=2017-09-03|website=[[H\u00fcrriyet]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/meral-aksenerin-partisinin-adiyla-ilgili-ipucu-40564241|title=Son Dakika: Meral Ak\u015fener'in kuraca\u011f\u0131 yeni partinin ismi belli oldu|last=|first=|date=2017-08-28|website=[[H\u00fcrriyet]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Positioning itself strictly at the centre of political spectrum, the party also advocates for a positive agenda which will bring the [[European Union]] and Turkey closer again, and highlights that Turkey must continue being a part of the [[Western Bloc|Western bloc]].<ref name=\"party program\"/><ref name=\"hurriyet.com.tr\"/> Meral Ak\u015fener was the party's [[2018 Turkish general election|2018 presidential candidate]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ensonhaber.com/meral-aksener-2019da-cumhurbaskani-adayi-olacak.html|title=Meral Ak\u015fener 2019'da Cumhurba\u015fkan\u0131 aday\u0131 olacak|website=Ensonhaber|accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe party quickly gained five [[Member of Parliament#Turkey|members of parliament]] in the [[Grand National Assembly]] who were originally elected for other parties, and numerous provincial and municipal council members that also defected from their former parties.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.birgun.net/haber-detay/mhp-li-meclis-uyesi-partisinden-istifa-edip-iyi-parti-ye-gecti-187004.html|title=MHP'li meclis \u00fcyesi partisinden istifa edip, \u0130Y\u0130 Parti'ye ge\u00e7ti|website=www.birgun.net}}</ref> On 22 April 2018, in the run-up to general elections, a further 15 [[Member of parliament|MP]]<nowiki/>s from the CHP moved to the \u0130yi Party following a joint agreement between the two parties. This was to allow the \u0130yi Party to form a parliamentary group that would be eligible to field a presidential candidate without the need to collect signatures and compete independently.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ba\u015faran|first1=R\u0131fat|title=CHP'den 15 milletvekili \u0130Y\u0130 Parti'ye ge\u00e7ti|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/son-dakika-iddiasi-chpden-15-milletvekili-iyi-partiye-gececek-40813377|website=H\u00fcrriyet|accessdate=22 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\n\n===MHP leadership challenge===\n{{main|2016 Nationalist Movement Party Extraordinary Congress}}\n\n[[Meral Ak\u015fener]], a former [[Ministry of the Interior (Turkey)|Minister of the Interior]] who served from 1996 to 1997, was a prominent [[Member of parliament#Turkey|member of parliament]] from the [[Nationalist Movement Party]] (MHP) from 2007 to November 2015, having been a member of the centre-right [[True Path Party (Turkey)|True Path Party]] (DYP) during her ministerial career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sozcu.com.tr/2017/gunun-icinden/meral-aksener-kimdir-kac-yasinda-nereli-yeni-partisinin-ismi-ne-aksener-parti-kuruyor-1993016/|title=Meral Ak\u015fener kimdir, ka\u00e7 ya\u015f\u0131nda, nereli, yeni partisinin ismi ne?|last=|first=|date=2017-08-29|website=[[S\u00f6zc\u00fc]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Her relation with MHP leader [[Devlet Bah\u00e7eli]] became noticeably strained after Bah\u00e7eli refused to nominate her for another term as [[Deputy Speaker of the Grand National Assembly]] after the [[June 2015 Turkish general election|June 2015 general election]], a post she had held since 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haberturk.com/gundem/haber/1094991-mhp-meclis-baskanvekilligi-icin-koray-aydini-belirledi|title=MHP, Meclis Ba\u015fkanvekilli\u011fi i\u00e7in Meral Ak\u015fener'in yerine Koray Ayd\u0131n'\u0131 belirledi|last=|first=|date=2015-06-25|website=Habert\u00fcrk|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Bah\u00e7eli eventually withdrew her parliamentary nomination before the [[November 2015 Turkish general election|November 2015 snap election]], resulting in her losing her parliamentary seat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/turkce/haberler/2015/09/150918_mhp_aksener_sinan_onus|title=MHP'de Meral Ak\u015fener s\u00fcrprizi|last=Onu\u015f|first=Sinan|date=2015-09-18|website=BBC T\u00fcrk\u00e7e|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe MHP, having won 16.29% of the vote and 80 seats in [[June 2015 Turkish general election|June 2015]], suffered a heavy defeat in the [[November 2015 Turkish general election|November snap election]] with just 11.90% of the vote and 40 seats. The loss was widely blamed on Bah\u00e7eli's refusal to consider any coalition agreement after the June 2015 election resulted in a [[hung parliament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/elections/2015/11/03/chp-mhp-and-hdp-destined-to-remain-in-opposition|title=CHP, MHP and HDP destined to remain in opposition|last=Paksoy|first=Yunus|date=2015-11-02|website=Daily Sabah|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The significant loss resulted in MHP dissidents including Ak\u015fener launching a drive to unseat Bah\u00e7eli from the party's leadership, a process made difficult by the party's strict bylaws. Other prominent MHP dissidents who declared their candidacy for the leadership included [[\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f]], [[Koray Ayd\u0131n]] and [[Sinan O\u011fan]]. \u00d6zda\u011f and Ayd\u0131n would eventually join Ak\u015fener in forming the \u0130yi Party, as did prominent MHP dissident MPs [[Yusuf Hala\u00e7o\u011flu]], {{Interlanguage link|\u0130smail Ok|tr||WD=}} and {{Interlanguage link|Nuri Okutan|tr||WD=}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://t24.com.tr/haber/yilan-hikayesine-donen-mhpnin-tuzuk-kurultayi-bugun,345961|title=MHP'de muhaliflerin ola\u011fan\u00fcst\u00fc kurultaydaki t\u00fcz\u00fck de\u011fi\u015fikli\u011fine y\u00f6nelik t\u00fcm \u00f6nergeleri kabul edildi|last=|first=|date=2016-06-19|website=T24|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:MHP 19 June Congress 2.jpg|thumb|MHP dissidents including Ak\u015fener hold an [[2016 Nationalist Movement Party Extraordinary Congress|extraordinary congress]], eventually nullified by the courts]]\nWith several MHP delegates supporting the dissidents' drive for a fresh leadership election, Ak\u015fener and the other leadership candidates joined forces to hold a constitutional convention, claiming they had the right to do so due to surpassing the required number of delegate signatures required. The MHP leadership boycotted the congress and declared it illegal, taking the process to court. The courts eventually upheld the claim that enough signatures had been submitted and forced the MHP leadership to hold a congress.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.bianet.org/bianet/siyaset/173768-mhp-de-muhalifler-kazandi-mahkeme-kurultay-karari-verdi|title=MHP'de Muhalifler Kazand\u0131, Mahkeme Kurultay Karar\u0131 Verdi|last=|first=|date=2016-04-08|website=Bianet|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In a controversial move, another court and the [[Supreme Electoral Council of Turkey]] (YSK) both struck down the ruling and asked the MHP leadership to not hold a congress.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diken.com.tr/ysk-kararini-verdi-mhpde-10-temmuzda-kongre-yapilamaz/|title=YSK karar\u0131n\u0131 verdi: MHP\u2019de 10 Temmuz\u2019da kongre yap\u0131lamaz - Diken|last=|first=|date=2016-06-28|website=Diken|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The move was widely seen as an interference in the judicial process and inner-party democracy by the governing [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|Justice and Development Party]] (AKP) and the [[Ministry of Justice]], which both had an interest in keeping the increasingly cooperative Bah\u00e7eli as MHP leader and preventing Ak\u015fener from mounting a challenge to the government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazetevatan.com/bekir-bozdag-dan-mhp-li-muhaliflere-cevap-944992-gundem/|title=Bekir Bozda\u011f'dan MHP'li muhaliflere cevap|last=|first=|date=2016-05-14|website=Vatan|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Ak\u015fener and several other dissidents were expelled from the party in the following months, mounting unsuccessful challenges against their suspensions. The constitutional convention held in June 2016 was annulled by the courts in January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tr.sputniknews.com/turkiye/201706201028963635-mhp-kongre-aksener-ogan-aydin-ozdag/|title=Mahkeme, MHP'nin tart\u0131\u015fmal\u0131 t\u00fcz\u00fck kurultay\u0131n\u0131 iptal etti|last=|first=|date=|website=tr.sputniknews.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===2017 constitutional referendum===\n{{main|2017 Turkish constitutional referendum}}\n[[File:MHP inner-party opposition No campaign 2.jpg|thumb|MHP dissidents hold a 'No' campaign event for the [[2017 Turkish constitutional referendum|2017 constitutional referendum]]]]\nIn December 2016, the governing AKP and opposition MHP agreed to put forward a joint constitutional amendment proposal that would change Turkey's [[parliamentary system]] into an [[executive presidency]]. The MHP's support for the proposals came as a surprise given the party's historically staunch opposition to an executive presidency.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ensonhaber.com/bahceli-anayasaya-neden-evet-dedigini-acikladi-2017-01-18.html|title=Bah\u00e7eli anayasaya neden evet dedi\u011fini a\u00e7\u0131klad\u0131|last=|first=|date=2017-01-18|website=Ensonhaber|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Many MHP members and prominent dissidents refused to support the party leadership and began their own 'No' campaigns. Polls and dissident politicians predicted that between 70\u201390% of MHP voters would defect from their party's official position and vote 'No'.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sozcu.com.tr/2017/gundem/mhp-evet-dese-bile-mhpli-hayir-diyecek-1679818/|title=MHP \u2018evet\u2019 dese bile MHP\u2019li \u2018hay\u0131r\u2019 diyecek|last=|first=|date=2017-02-15|website=[[S\u00f6zc\u00fc]] |publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAk\u015fener, Okutan, Hala\u00e7o\u011flu and \u00d6zda\u011f all became prominent 'No' campaigners, with many political commentators seeing the alliance as a signal of a forthcoming new political party united under Ak\u015fener's leadership.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sozcu.com.tr/2017/gundem/mhpli-muhalifler-hayir-kampanyasini-baslatti-1686815/|title=MHP\u2019li muhalifler \u2018Hay\u0131r\u2019 kampanyas\u0131n\u0131 ba\u015flatt\u0131|last=|first=|date=2017-02-18|website=[[S\u00f6zc\u00fc]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The referendum was very controversial due to a last-minute change in the ballot counting procedure by the [[Supreme Electoral Council of Turkey|Supreme Electoral Council]], causing the dissident nationalists and other 'No' campaigners to allege fraud and not recognise the results.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/turkce/haberler-turkiye-39613985|title='M\u00fch\u00fcrs\u00fcz oy' tart\u0131\u015fmalar\u0131n\u0131n hukuki boyutu ne?|last=\u00d6zdemir|first=\u00d6zge |date=17 April 2017|website=bbc.com|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> According to official results, the 'No' side lost with 48.6% of the vote to 'Yes's 51.4%, though Ak\u015fener alleged that the actual result was a victory for 'No' by a margin of 52\u201348%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haberler.com/meral-aksener-hayir-in-orani-yuzde-52-9508758-haberi/|title=Meral Ak\u015fener: YSK'ya G\u00f6re 'Hay\u0131r'\u0131n Oran\u0131 Y\u00fczde 52, Evet Y\u00fczde 48|last=|first=|date=2017-04-16|website=Haberler.com|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Party preparations===\nFollowing the [[2017 Turkish constitutional referendum]], it was announced that MHP dissidents would unite under a new party led by Ak\u015fener, with the party's official announcement expected in September or October 2017. During its preparation period, the party was touted as a 'nationalist conservative' alternative to the MHP and the AKP, while endorsing the [[Kemalism|principles]] of [[Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk]].<ref name=\"haberturk.com\"/> The party was also described to be strictly [[Centrism|centrist]]. During the establishment preparations, the names of 'Centrist Democrat Party' ''(Merkez Demokrat Parti)'' and 'Mainland Party' ''(Anayurt Partisi)'' were alleged to have been selected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mynet.com/haber/politika/meral-aksenerin-yeni-partisi-merkez-demokrat-partinin-logosu-sizdirildi-3227681-1|title=Meral Ak\u015fener'in yeni partisi Merkez Demokrat Parti'nin logosu s\u0131zd\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131|last=|first=|date=2017-08-30|website=Mynet|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/siyaset/822520/Meral_Aksener_in_kuracagi_partinin_logosu_belli_oldu.html|title=Meral Ak\u015fener'in kuraca\u011f\u0131 partinin logosu belli oldu|last=|first=|date=2017-09-13|website=[[Cumhuriyet]]|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Formation==\n{{see also|\u0130Y\u0130 Party founding convention, 2017}}\n[[File:\u0130Y\u0130 Party establishment 3.jpg|thumb|\u0130yi Party supporters at the party's launch event, 25 October 2017]]\n[[File:KAYI BOYU DAMGASI.svg|thumb|The [[Kay\u0131 tribe]] flag from which the party takes its name]]\nThe party was announced at a congress at the [[N\u00e2z\u0131m Hikmet Cultural Centre]] in [[Ankara]] on 25 October 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Meral Ak\u015fener'in Partisi, 25 Ekim'de Kuruluyor|url=https://www.haberler.com/meral-aksener-partisinin-kurulus-tarihini-10153689-haberi/|accessdate=25 October 2017|work=Haberler|date=20 October 2017}}</ref> On that day, the party's name, logo and slogan were revealed to the public. Meral Ak\u015fener was formally elected as the party's first leader\u2014unopposed, carrying all votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mynet.com/haber/politika/son-dakika-meral-aksener-genel-baskan-secildi-3345004-1|title=Meral Ak\u015fener genel ba\u015fkan se\u00e7ildi|last=|first=|date=2017-10-25|website=Mynet|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Legal disputes and challenges===\n\nThe party's name, logo and slogan were immediately subject to legal challenges and controversy, with allegations that they bore resemblance to [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|AKP]] [[Antalya]] Mayor [[Menderes T\u00fcrel]]'s [[2014 Turkish local elections|2014 local election]] campaign. T\u00fcrel issued a statement claiming that he owned the patents as of 24 October 2015. The AKP Mayor of [[Bilecik]], Selim Ya\u011fc\u0131, threatened legal action alleging that the logo was stolen from the official seal of [[Bilecik Province]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.birgun.net/haber-detay/akp-li-bilecik-belediyesi-iyi-parti-ye-dava-aciyor-187555.html|title=AKP'li Bilecik Belediyesi \u0130yi Parti'ye dava a\u00e7\u0131yor|last=|first=|date=2017-10-30|website=www.birgun.net|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The [[Kay\u0131 tribe]] Association also announced legal challenges, claiming that they had the patent to the flag since 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internethaber.com/iyi-partiye-bir-dava-daha-patentini-2014te-aldik-1819254h.htm|title=\u0130yi Parti'ye bir dava daha! Patentini 2014'te ald\u0131k|last=|first=|date=2017-10-30|website=internet Haber|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> A former AKP mayoral candidate alleged that the party's slogan belonged to him and threatened legal challenges if the party refused to stop using it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haberturk.com/iyi-parti-ni-sloganina-patent-engeli-1687176|title=\u0130yi Parti'nin slogan\u0131na patent engeli|last=|first=|date=2017-10-25|website=Habert\u00fcrk|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Preparation for 2018 elections===\n{{Main|Meral Ak\u015fener presidential campaign, 2018}}\nMeral Ak\u015fener will be the party's [[2018 Turkish general election|2018 presidential candidate]], but will not stand for election as an [[Member of parliament#Turkey|MP]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gazeteduvar.com.tr/politika/2017/12/29/meral-aksener-cumhurbaskanligina-aday-olacagim/|title=Meral Ak\u015fener: Cumhurba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131\u2019na aday olaca\u011f\u0131m|last=|first=|date=2017-12-29|website=|publisher=Gazete Duvar|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Some [[Opinion polling for the next Turkish general election|opinion polls]] have predicted her personal support at up to 40%, and her party's support for parliamentary elections between 5% and 20%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tr.sputniknews.com/turkiye/201711011030835512-gezici-aksener-erken-secim-oy-dagilimi-aksener/|title=Gezici anketi: Ak\u015fener'in partisi erken se\u00e7imde y\u00fczde 19.5 oy al\u0131yor|first=|last=Sputnik|website=tr.sputniknews.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://t24.com.tr/haber/mak-danismanlik-erdogani-desteklerim-diyenlerin-orani-yuzde-48-meclise-sadece-akp-ve-chp-girebiliyor,464382|title=MAK Dan\u0131\u015fmanl\u0131k: \"Erdo\u011fan'\u0131 desteklerim\" diyenlerin oran\u0131 y\u00fczde 48, Meclis'e sadece AKP ve CHP girebiliyor|last=|first=|date=2017-10-14|website=T24|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Ideology and policies==\n\n[[File:Meral Ak\u015fener \u0130Y\u0130 Party 2.jpg|thumb|[[Meral Ak\u015fener]] giving her first speech as party leader, 25 October 2017]]\n\u0130yi Party has been described as a [[Turkish nationalism|Turkish nationalist]], [[Conservatism|conservative]] and [[Kemalism|Atat\u00fcrkist]] political party that adopts [[centrism]] as its official political position.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.birgun.net/haber-detay/aksener-in-kurulacak-yeni-partisi-icin-bir-isim-onerisi-daha-177478.html|title=Ak\u015fener'in kurulacak yeni partisi i\u00e7in bir isim \u00f6nerisi daha|last=|first=|date=2017-09-01|website=www.birgun.net|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> However, it is generally regarded as a [[Centre right|centre-right]] political force designed to fill the void left by the traditionally right-leaning parties, namely the governing [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|Justice and Development Party]] (AKP) and the [[Nationalist Movement Party]] (MHP).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bursadabugun.com/haber/chp-den-iyi-parti-hakkinda-ilk-aciklama-886003.html|title=CHP'den \u0130Y\u0130 Parti hakk\u0131nda ilk a\u00e7\u0131klama|last=|first=|date=2017-10-26|website=bursadabugun.com|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.habererk.com/siyaset/kilicdaroglu-meral-aksener-siyasi-boslugu-gordu-h38421.html|title=K\u0131l\u0131\u00e7daro\u011flu: \"Meral Ak\u015fener siyasi bo\u015flu\u011fu g\u00f6rd\u00fc\"|last=|first=|date=2017-08-17|website=www.habererk.com|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Statements made by prominent party members have also espoused a fresh perspective on [[Turkish politics]], criticising the [[Anti-establishment|established political parties]] for incompetence, ineffectiveness and polarising the electorate.\n\nAlthough the party described itself as [[National conservatism|nationalist conservative]] during its formation period, its ideology represents [[civic nationalism]] rather than the MHP's ardent ethnic nationalism.<ref name=\"haberturk.com\"/> The party espouses harmony between ethnic minorities and tolerance for different religions and backgrounds, rejecting any discrimination on ethnic, gender or religious grounds.<ref name=\"internethaber.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.internethaber.com/aksenerin-yeni-partisinin-ismi-koray-aydin-acikladi-1803848h.htm|title=Ak\u015fener'in yeni partisinin ismi Koray Ayd\u0131n a\u00e7\u0131klad\u0131|last=|first=|date=2017-08-29|website=internet Haber|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> It is strongly in favour of the [[Kemalism|ideals and principles]] of Turkey's founding president, [[Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://t24.com.tr/haber/yusuf-halacoglu-kurulacak-yeni-partiyi-anlatti-milliyetci-muhafazakar-ve-ataturkcu-olacak,420573|title=Yusuf Hala\u00e7o\u011flu kurulacak yeni partiyi anlatt\u0131: Milliyet\u00e7i, muhafazak\u00e2r ve Atat\u00fcrk\u00e7\u00fc olacak|last=|first=|date=2017-08-18|website=T24|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe party's centrist and Atat\u00fcrkist stance has attracted support from traditionally centre-left [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]] voters. [[Aytun \u00c7\u0131ray]], the party's general secretary, is also a former CHP member. The party has also attracted support from the left-leaning [[Democratic Left Party (Turkey)|Democratic Left Party]] (DSP), reinforcing itself as a party for all voters regardless of left-right affiliation.<ref name=\"internethaber.com\"/>\n\n=== Women's rights ===\nThe party, fielding the first woman candidate for Turkish presidency in history, puts great emphasis on [[women's rights in Turkey]] and made this a central part of its election campaign. It highlights the statistics and draws attention to the drastic increase of cases of [[violence against women]] and [[rape]] in Turkey under AKP administration. Ak\u015fener declared her pledge to lift [[good conduct time]] in all cases of violence against women and rape, and instead of forcefully sending women to therapy in such cases, her party will be sending the perpetrator to mandatory therapy before or after serving their sentence and therapy for women will be optional.<ref name=\"women\">{{cite news |title=Ak\u015fener: Kad\u0131nlara \u015fiddet ve tecav\u00fczde 'iyi hal indirimi'ni kald\u0131raca\u011f\u0131m |url=http://www.abcgazetesi.com/aksener-kadinlara-siddet-ve-tecavuzde-iyi-hal-indirimini-kaldiracagim-88824h.htm |publisher=ABC |date=7 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nAk\u015fener also reminded the rejected government bill in November 2016 which attempted to make it possible for 12-year-old girls to marry and religious marriages to be considered fully legal, and told that she found this \"disgusting\" and \"saw this as a by-product of the male-dominant structure of politics\" and declared that she will make sure that no such bill will even be considered under her administration.<ref name=\"women\"/> She highlighted that in the last decade women has become afraid to go on street alone and wear what they want and pledged that under her administration it will be her moral duty to make all women be comfortable with their lifestyle and she will tackle violence and abuse against women and [[child abuse|children]] in a way that no perpetrator will even be able to think of it.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kolcu |first1=Gamze |title=Ak\u015fener: Sorunlar\u0131 kad\u0131n g\u00f6z\u00fcyle, y\u00fcre\u011fiyle \u00e7\u00f6zmek i\u00e7in yola \u00e7\u0131kt\u0131k |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/aksener-sorunlari-kadin-gozuyle-yuregiyle-cozmek-icin-yola-ciktik-40855889 |publisher=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |date=2 June 2018}}</ref> Ak\u015fener announced that her movement starts a ''T\u00fclbent Revolution'', named after a piece of clothing which women wear to cover their heads partially, in rural Turkey, which is a [[Turkish folk dress|traditional]] Turkish but not a religious clothing associated with political Islam. She stated \"if men can not unite and keep fighting, a woman rises up, takes the ''t\u00fclbent'' off her head and throws it on the ground and the nation reconciles\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Meral Ak\u015fener \u00e7\u0131lg\u0131n projesini a\u00e7\u0131klad\u0131: T\u00fclbent devrimi |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/turkiye/meral-aksener-cilgin-projesini-acikladi-tulbent-devrimi |publisher=[[CNN T\u00fcrk]] |date=2 June 2018}}</ref> She explained that \"youth in Turkey do not see the differences of the past, (...) girls having tattoos and girls wearing the headscarf, and boys having piercings, they do not see each other different\". She went on to state that T\u00fclbent Revolution will be a symbol for reconciliation of different lifestyles in Turkey and that respect here is more important than tolerance because tolerance usually describes a majority's behavior upon a minority and that is not the case in [[Turkish people|Turkish society]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=D\u00fcndar |first1=U\u011fur |title=U\u011fur D\u00fcndar ile Halk Arenas\u0131 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0HH9d_tXJEA |website=YouTube |publisher=[[Halk TV]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ak\u015fener'den Ahlat\u2019ta bayram sofras\u0131: Bir hayalim var |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/aksenerden-ahlatta-bayram-sofrasi-bir-hayalim-var-40868620 |publisher=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |date=15 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nAk\u015fener, contrary to political party establishment in Turkey, refused to set up a \"Women's Wing\" for her party advocating that this discriminates against women in essence and instead, introduced a mandatory quota of 25% women participance for all branches and candidates of her party, including the general administrative board. She further stated that she actually wanted the quota to be at 30% but the mutual decision was 25% to begin with.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ak\u015fener: \u0130Y\u0130 Parti bir kad\u0131n hareketidir |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/aksener-iyi-parti-bir-kadin-siyaset-2567431/ |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |date=6 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlthough there was an increase in participation of women in the workforce in the last decades in Turkey, Ak\u015fener states she still finds this inadequate and will implement [[benevolent sexism]] to increase participation of [[women in workforce]] and to reduce the [[Gender pay gap|wage gap]].<ref name=\"women\"/>\n\nDescribed as the Iron Lady of Turkey, during an interview with ''[[The Guardian]]'' Ak\u015fener said: \"Now it is time for them, the men in power, to feel fear\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Saracoglu |first1=Gokce |title=Turkey's iron lady: 'It's time for the men in power to feel fear' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/03/turkey-meral-aksener-time-for-the-men-in-power-to-feel-fear |publisher=[[The Guardian]] |date=3 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Animal rights ===\nCurrently the law protecting the animal rights in Turkey is vague and not comprehensive and only allows limited monetary compensations for pet owners in cases of harm against their \"property\". This allowed many cases of intense violence against animals, mostly done by perpetrators just for entertainment, creating public outrage and calls for animal rights laws to be made comprehensive and deterrent punishments to be introduced.<ref>{{cite web |last1=\u00d6zg\u00fcner |first1=Burak |title=T\u00fcrkiye\u2019de Hayvan Haklar\u0131: Ne Yasa Ne Tasa! |url=https://m.bianet.org/biamag/hayvan-haklari/189030-turkiye-de-hayvan-haklari-ne-yasa-ne-tasa |publisher=[[Bianet]]}}</ref> Ak\u015fener, historically being an animal rights volunteer through her career, has been regarded as the most outspoken candidate for protection of [[animal rights]] and against the drastic increase of violation of these rights in Turkey.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ak\u015fener'den hayvan haklar\u0131 s\u00f6z\u00fc |url=https://tr.sputniknews.com/turkiye/201805111033396175-meral-aksener-iyi-parti-hayvan-haklari/ |publisher=Sputnik |date=11 May 2018}}</ref> Upon calls by the Confederation of Animal Rights Associations of Turkey, entitled \"No votes for candidates ignoring animal rights\", Ak\u015fener was first to gather with 250 NGO representatives working on the field and was the first candidate to sign the [[covenant (law)|covenant]] of animal rights issued by the confederation of NGOs,<ref>{{cite web |title=Eylem Araz \u0130Y\u0130 Parti Genel Ba\u015fkan\u0131 ve Cumhurba\u015fkan\u0131 Aday\u0131 Say\u0131n Meral Ak\u015fener Hayvan Haklar\u0131 \u0130\u00e7in \u2018S\u00f6z Verdi\u2019 |url=http://www.haykonfed.org/2018/05/12/iyi-parti-genel-baskani-ve-cumhurbaskani-adayi-sayin-meral-aksener-hayvan-haklari-icin-soz-verdi/ |publisher=HAYKONFED}}</ref> followed only by [[Peoples' Democratic Party (Turkey)|HDP]] candidate [[Selahattin Demirta\u015f]] 2 weeks later .<ref>{{cite news |title=Meral Ak\u015fener ve Selahattin Demirta\u015f Hayvan Haklar\u0131 Taahh\u00fctnamesi'ni imzalad\u0131 |url=http://t24.com.tr/haber/meral-aksener-ve-selahattin-demirtas-hayvan-haklari-taahhutnamesini-imzaladi,640950 |publisher={{Interlanguage link|T24 (newspaper)|lt=T24|tr|T24}} |date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn February, while in western coastal city of [[\u0130zmir]] for a political rally, Ak\u015fener personally adopted a cat named ''Cedric'', which was raped earlier and was found covered in blood on a street in [[Fo\u00e7a]] and repeated her calls and pledge for comprehensive and deterrent animal rights laws in Turkey.<ref>{{cite news |last1=K\u00fc\u00e7\u00fck Cantank |first1=Nilay |title=M\u0130T\u0130NG \u0130\u00c7\u0130N \u0130ZM\u0130R\u2019E G\u0130DEN MERAL AK\u015eENER TECAV\u00dcZE U\u011eRAYAN KED\u0130 CEDR\u0130C\u2019\u0130 SAH\u0130PLEND\u0130 |url=https://www.ajanimo.com/miting-icin-izmire-giden-meral-aksener-tecavuze-ugrayan-kedi-cedrici-sahiplendi/ |publisher=Ajanimo |date=20 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n\u0130yi Party's program also reserves a whole section for animal rights and mentions pledges including \"making animal rights a public demand through intense awareness and consciousness efforts\", \"full adoption of [[UNESCO]] Animal Rights Declaration\", \"active and effective wildlife protection\", \"scientific research and tracking of [[endangered species]] in Turkey\", \"strict regulation and bans when necessary on [[hunting]], animal farms, [[animal racing]], animal shows, pet shops, [[animal shelters]] and all commercial activities focusing on animals\".<ref name=\"program\">{{cite web |title=\u0130Y\u0130 Party Program |url=http://iyiparti.org.tr/Assets/pdf/iyi_parti_programi.pdf |publisher=\u0130yi Party}}</ref>\n\n=== EU and European integration ===\nAt a time of increased political tensions between [[EU-Turkey relations|EU and Turkey]] due to Erdo\u011fan's [[Anti-Europeanism|Anti-EU]] [[Right wing populism|populist]] rhetoric, Ak\u015fener and her party promoting [[pro-Europeanism]], has become one of the movements which is most openly in favor of the continuation of [[European integration|European integration of Turkey]] and positive close relations between EU and Turkey, at the same time managing to appeal to conservative and nationalist right-wing voters.<ref name=\"deutsche welle\"/><ref name=\"program\"/>\n\nDuring her [[Nationalist Movement Party|MHP]] days as [[Deputy Speaker of the Grand National Assembly]], even back in 2010, Ak\u015fener held a pro-EU stance and was many times part of meetings with EU officials representing Turkey, and was described as the head of the European-leaning wing inside the nationalist party, [[Nationalist Movement Party|MHP]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Meral Ak\u015fener'den AB'ye mesaj |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/meral-aksener-den-ab-ye-mesaj-siyaset-1238033/ |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |date=14 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to committed pledges of mainstream social democrat main-opposition [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|CHP]] and left-wing minority rights [[Peoples' Democratic Party (Turkey)|HDP]], Ak\u015fener's \u0130yi also declares her party's main goal as [[Accession of Turkey into the EU|full membership to the EU]] and rejects former suggestions made such as \"privileged partnership\", stating this puts Turkey into a secondary position. However, contrary to other pro-EU parties, the party also does not refrain from criticizing the certain attitudes implemented by EU in the past process in its party program, stating that \"Positive EU-Turkey relations are vital for EU as vital as they are to Turkey, but [[de facto]] freeze of the full membership process and negotiations is not only because of Turkey's inability to satisfy all the membership requirements but also because of EU's policy towards Turkey being shaped through interior fears in line with rising racist sentiment across EU in the last years.\" Party program then advocates for the continuation of Turkish integration into EU and goal of full membership but also states the formula for positive relations and integration, with remarks such as \"with its current state, EU-Turkey relations do not benefit any side when in fact it can, and such positive and healthy relations between two entities will not only benefit both sides but also the [[Balkans]], [[Caucasus|Caucasia]], [[Middle East]] and the [[Eastern Mediterranean]]. Thus, the crucial EU-Turkey relations will be freed from the influence of racist sentiment in EU and dysfunctioning full membership process in Turkey and the negotiations process will be revitalized and EU-Turkey relations will positively be redefined\", bearing the goal of full membership and open support for positive relations and participation in integration, whether with or without full membership.<ref name=\"program\"/><ref name=\"election\">{{cite web |title=Milletimizle S\u00f6zle\u015fme (Accord with the Nation) |url=http://iyiparti.org.tr/assets/pdf/secim_beyani.pdf |publisher=\u0130yi Parti}}</ref>\n\nOn December 15, Ak\u015fener met with the ambassadors of the EU countries led by Christian Berger, head of EU Delegation in Turkey at party headquarters. She rejected to read from a script and talked directly about her opinions, declaring her party's position as full membership to the EU and continuation of the dialogue through membership negotiations and supplementary mechanisms. She stated that \"she is against any mindset which scraps Turkey off from Europe and EU\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=G\u00fcven\u00e7 |first1=Duygu |title=\u0130kinci turda kazanaca\u011f\u0131m |url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/siyaset/887128/_ikinci_turda_kazanacagim_.html |publisher=[[Cumhuriyet]] |date=15 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn an interview with [[Euronews]] on February 26, Ak\u015fener criticized Erdogan's recent [[Euroskepticism|anti-European]] rhetoric stating that \"EU has always been a measure of success in Turkey and the ruling party also, although conflicting with their mindset, due to the political reality of the time, took big steps towards EU from 2002 to 2007. Only after this date, for the first time ever, EU has been started to be depicted as a monster and an enemy in Turkey. We do not agree with that and we see the [[European integration|European project]] as the first time after the [[French Revolution]] in Europe where logic and rationality rules above all the other ideas\". She also stated that \"with great sadness I also see that recently the same irrational rhetoric used by Erdogan is being picked up by some leaders of the EU\", then advising about the need to free both sides from such rhetoric and the necessity to set a positive ground drawing two entities closer together, in line with [[Atat\u00fcrk]]\u2032s ''peace in the homeland, peace in the world'' principle and the 160-year-old European character of [[Foreign relations of Turkey|Turkish foreign policy]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ak\u015fener: F\u0131rat'\u0131n do\u011fusu asla g\u00f6zden ka\u00e7\u0131r\u0131lmamal\u0131d\u0131r |url=http://tr.euronews.com/2018/02/26/aksener-f-rat-n-dogusu-asla-gozden-kac-r-lmamal-d-r |publisher=[[Euronews]] |date=26 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn May 8, one day before the [[Europe Day]], Meral Ak\u015fener met with the [[Germany|German]] [[Federal Foreign Office|Minister of State for Europe]] [[Michael Roth (politician)|Michael Roth]] at party headquarters and focused on upcoming elections and [[Germany-Turkey relations|German-Turkish partnership]] and EU-Turkey relations. During the press briefing Ak\u015fener made strong remarks which had a broad repercussion in national and European press, saying \"Turkey is Europe. It is also beneficial for EU to gain this mindset. In line with that, states must have such positive perspectives to solve their issues.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Alman bakandan Meral Ak\u015fener'e ziyaret |url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/turkiye/971162/Alman_bakandan_Meral_Aksener_e_ziyaret.html |publisher=[[Cumhuriyet]] |date=8 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ak\u015fener |first1=Meral |title=Official Account |url=https://twitter.com/meral_aksener/status/993765873151303680 |publisher=Twitter}}</ref>\n\nOne day later, this position and party's pro-European stance was further strengthened when Meral Ak\u015fener and the party were the only political figures openly celebrating the Europe Day and delivering positive messages in Turkey on May 9. Ak\u015fener re-affirmed her message that \"states must have positive perspectives to solve such issues to make the region a better place\" referring to EU-Turkey relations revitalizing and congratulated everyone's Europe Day on her official [[Twitter]] account.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ak\u015fener |first1=Meral |title=Official Account |url=https://twitter.com/meral_aksener/status/994242800936943616 |publisher=Twitter}}</ref>\n\nMeanwhile, \u0130yi Party released a public press statement celebrating the Europe Day and making strong remarks, further bolstering party position with regards to EU affairs. The statement included remarks such as \"We see European Union as a project of democracy, rule of law, personal rights and freedoms, peace and prosperity. Today, protecting and implementing these [[European values]] are more important than ever. Sustainability of the assertivity of the EU depends on its ability to prevent the interior threatening factions and movements and to keep its vision wide. Full membership to a European Union which sincerely protects its founding values, conforms to ''[[pacta sunt servanda]]'' and which looks to its European future with trust, undoubtedly, is a desired goal for Turkey, which is a natural member of [[Europe]] and an [[EU Candidate]] since 1999. \u0130yi Party's biggest goal is to re-implement democracy, rule of law and personal rights and freedoms according to highest norms. In line with this, under \u0130yi Party administration, suitable with Turkey's historical inclination and European character, full membership of Turkey to the EU, will contribute vastly to the creation of a Europe which is strong, reliable, dynamic and prosper.\" The declaration concluded with Ak\u015fener's previous remarks \"We can live in a better region and world if states approach to solving issues with positive perspectives. We congratulate the Europe Day of all our citizens and our European friends and allies\"<ref>{{cite web |title=9 May\u0131s Avrupa G\u00fcn\u00fcne ili\u015fkin \u0130Y\u0130 Parti bas\u0131n a\u00e7\u0131klamas\u0131. |url=https://twitter.com/iyiparti/status/994260045021040640 |website=Twitter |publisher=\u0130Y\u0130 Parti Official Page}}</ref>\n\nOther political heavyweights of the party also reaffirmed party's [[Pro-European]] position and full membership goals including \u0130yi Party MP representing \u0130zmir and party speaker [[Aytun \u00c7\u0131ray]], making a press briefing at parliament on January 9, stating \"As stated by [[Emmanuel Macron|President Macron]], under state of emergency and rule by decree conditions, continuing negotiations and membership dialogue between EU and Turkey is not possible. We also do not accept partnership model suggestions which put Turkey into a secondary position such as \"privileged partnership\". \u0130yi Party will put an end to state of emergency, re-instate democracy and rule of law in Turkey and will be the movement which gives Turkey what it deserves, full membership to the European Union.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=\u00c7\u0131ray |first1=Aytun |title=\u0130Y\u0130 PART\u0130 GENEL SEKRETER\u0130, \u0130ZM\u0130R M\u0130LLETVEK\u0130L\u0130 AYTUN \u00c7IRAY: \u0130Y\u0130 PART\u0130 T\u00dcRK\u0130YE\u2019Y\u0130 HAK ETT\u0130\u011e\u0130 G\u0130B\u0130 AB TAM \u00dcYES\u0130 YAPACAKTIR |url=http://iyiparti.org.tr/basin-aciklamasi/iyi-parti-turkiye-yi-hak-ettigi-gibi-ab-tam-uyesi-yapacaktir |publisher=\u0130yi Party |date=9 January 2018}}</ref> Party vice chairman and MP representing [[Gaziantep]], [[\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f]], voiced his notion that Turkey should stay as an integral part of [[Western bloc]] and \"as a student who studied in Europe and having a big respect for their culture and values\", advocated for positive and closer relations with EU in August 2017, before the formation of the party.<ref>{{cite news |last1=\u00d6zbey |first1=\u0130pek |title=\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f: Merkez sa\u011f de\u011fil milli merkez |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/umit-ozdag-merkez-sag-degil-milli-merkez-40549074 |publisher=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |date=13 August 2017}}</ref> After the formation, on an interview with [[Cumhuriyet]], he explained that EU and Turkey must reshape their relations and put it on a positive path, highlighting that both entities are very much in need of each other, positive relations and cooperation, [[Refugee crisis]], being the latest example.<ref>{{cite news |last1=S\u00f6nmez |first1=Atakan |title=\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f: AKP'den ald\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z oy CHP'den ald\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z\u0131n 3 kat\u0131 |url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/siyaset/994816/Umit_Ozdag__AKP_den_aldigimiz_oy_CHP_den_aldigimizin_3_kati.html |publisher=[[Cumhuriyet]] |date=11 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== NATO ===\n\u0130yi Party holds a strict position highlighting that it is crucial for Turkey to continue being part of the [[Western bloc]], thus [[NATO]] and is of best national interest.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f yeni parti program\u0131n\u0131n \u015fifrelerini anlatt\u0131 |url=https://www.ulusal.com.tr/gundem/umit-ozdag-yeni-parti-programinin-sifrelerini-anlatti-h173031.html |publisher=Ulusal |date=14 August 2017}}</ref> Party program openly states that following the [[Second World War]] and [[Cold War]], integration of Turkey into Western bloc has been very beneficial and functional defence policies and country's national interests still lie on equal cooperation with the rest of the bloc.<ref name=\"program\"/>\n\nVice chairman \u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f also does not refrain from criticizing certain moves by other NATO members too and highlights that due to wrong policies implemented by Erdo\u011fan, [[Members of NATO|NATO allies of Turkey]] started to incline taking steps sometimes that threaten the national security of Turkey. With regards to that, \u00d6zda\u011f states that their administration will not pursue such wrong policies, but will stay as a cooperative member while protecting the Turkish national security at all times as a member, which AKP fails to do so.<ref>{{cite news |last1=S\u00f6nmez |first1=Atakan |title=\u00dcmit \u00d6zda\u011f: AKP'den ald\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z oy CHP'den ald\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z\u0131n 3 kat\u0131 |url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/siyaset/994816/Umit_Ozdag__AKP_den_aldigimiz_oy_CHP_den_aldigimizin_3_kati.html |publisher=Cumhuriyet |date=11 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nAk\u015fener also heavily criticized the move by [[Erdo\u011fan]] administration to buy [[S-400 missile system]]s from Russia in a move to distance the country from NATO and the West and get closer to [[Russia]], stating that the move lacks common sense and wisdom and invited Erdo\u011fan for calmness and to have \"information on history\". Ak\u015fener explained that the move makes no sense as the missiles are not compatible with the whole, decades-long existing structure of the [[Turkish military|Turkish military and defence]], which also is integrated to common NATO defence systems, saying that in case of conclusion of such a purchase and its delivery, the S400 missiles will just rot in hangars. She went on to say that such moves by the ruling [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|AKP]] seriously dishonored and degraded [[Foreign relations of Turkey|Turkey's foreign policy]], conflicting with 150-years old Turkish foreign policy principals and making it worthless and under her administration, \u0130yi Party will put an end to this trend.<ref>{{cite news |title=Meral Ak\u015fener'den 'S-400' tepkisi: Koyacaks\u0131n depoya \u00e7\u00fcr\u00fcyecekler |url=http://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/siyaset/895172/Meral_Aksener_den__S-400__tepkisi__Koyacaksin_depoya_curuyecekler.html |publisher=Cumhuriyet |date=29 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nParty spokesperson and MP [[Aytun \u00c7\u0131ray]] also criticized the move stating that the country which AKP moves to buy missile systems from fully supports organizations aiming to harm and destabilize Turkey and such moves by the ruling party are implemented through their \"ideological obsessions\" and \"learned ignorance\", put Turkey towards a dead-end. He went on to make a strong remark, criticizing the recent [[pro-Russian]] moves of Erdo\u011fan which shift Turkey away from the Western bloc and closer to Russia, stating that \"never ever since the administration of [[Mahmud Nedim Pasha]]...\", 19th century [[grand vizier]] of the [[Turkish Empire]], who was highly under influence of Russian officials and was subserviant to [[Imperial Russia]], earning him the nickname ''Nedimoff'', \"...Turkey and its foreign policy has been held hostage like this\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Aytun \u00c7\u0131ray: S-400 ald\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z Rusya, YPG'ye tam destek veriyor  Kaynak Yeni\u00e7a\u011f: Aytun \u00c7\u0131ray: S-400 ald\u0131\u011f\u0131m\u0131z Rusya, YPG'ye tam destek veriyor |url=http://www.yenicaggazetesi.com.tr/aytun-ciray-s-400-aldigimiz-rusya-ypgye-tam-destek-veriyor-188340h.htm |publisher=Yeni\u00e7a\u011f |date=30 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Personal rights and freedoms and media freedom===\n{{Empty section|date=July 2019}}\n\n===Economy===\n{{Empty section|date=July 2018}}\n\n==Political program==\n\nAs described in its official party program, the primary goals set by \u0130yi Party are to:<ref name=\"party program\"/>\n* Make Turkey one of the top 10 economies of the world\n* Raise the average national income to US$14,500 within five years\n* Achieve an average education age of 11 years\n* Achieve a 100% [[literacy rate]] for women under 40 within five years\n* Be among the top 40 countries in the [[Legatum Prosperity Index]] within five years\n* Have 50 million foreign tourists spending an average of US$1,000 visit Turkey every year\n* Return to the parliamentary system with a new constitution within the first year\n* Create a democratic political parties law within the first year\n* Achieve 150,000 hectares of plantation and erosion control per year\n* Be among the top 20 countries in the global [[Programme for International Student Assessment|PISA]] education ranking\n* Lower the unemployment rate to 8% within five years\n* Achieve the [[Fourth Industrial Revolution]] and implement [[Industry 4.0]]\n* Spread the positive energy of women and youth throughout society\n* Immediately implement [[European Union]] standards in press freedom\n* Make [[Turkish passport]]s valuable and reputable\n\nSpecific key policies include an effective counter-terrorism strategy against members of the [[G\u00fclen Movement]] (FET\u00d6) that have been alleged to be behind the [[2016 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat attempt|failed coup attempt]] in July 2016. The party identifies FET\u00d6 as the \"most serious internal threat\" to national security.<ref name=\"sozcu.com.tr\"/> Another key policy is a reversal of the changes adopted in the controversial [[2017 Turkish constitutional referendum|2017 constitutional referendum]], which would revert Turkey to a [[parliamentary republic]] as opposed to an [[executive presidency]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nThe party also vowed to lift the [[2017 block of Wikipedia in Turkey]] on the first day after the elections.<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=2018-05-25|title=\u0130yi Parti: Se\u00e7imi kazan\u0131rsak Wikipedia'y\u0131 a\u00e7aca\u011f\u0131z|url=http://www.abcgazetesi.com/iyi-parti-secimi-kazanirsak-wikipediayi-acacagiz-85507h.htm|newspaper=ABC Gazetesi|language=tr}}</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ [[Grand National Assembly of Turkey]]\n! rowspan=2| Election\n! rowspan=2| Leader\n! colspan=3| Votes\n! colspan=2| Seats\n! rowspan=2| Government\n|-\n! style=\"width:50px\"| #\n! style=\"width:50px\"| %\n! style=\"width:50px\"| Rank\n! style=\"width:50px\"| #\n! style=\"width:50px\"| \u00b1\n|-\n! [[2018 Turkish parliamentary election|2018]]\n| [[Meral Ak\u015fener]]\n| 4,990,710\n| 9.96\n| 5th\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''{{Composition bar compact|42|600|{{\u0130yi Party/meta/color}}|#d40000|text-shadow=no}}'''\n| ''new''\n| {{no2|[[People's Alliance (Turkey)|AKP]]}}\n|}\n\n=== Presidential elections ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; border:none;width:100%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|Presidential election record of \u0130Y\u0130 Party\n|-\n! !! Election !! Candidate !! Votes !! % !! Outcome !! width=230px| Map\n|-\n| || '''[[2018 Turkish presidential election|24 June 2018]]''' || [[File:Meral Ak\u015fener \u0130Y\u0130 Party (cropped)1.jpg|76px]]<hr>[[Meral&nbsp;Ak\u015fener]] || 3,649,030 || 7.29% || '''4th''' || [[File:\u0130yiParti2018.png|220px]]\n|}\n\n=== Local elections ===\n[[File:2019 Turkish local elections IYI.png|right|thumb|Party's performance in the [[2019 Turkish local elections]] by province.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:0.906em; width:60%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:gray; color:white; text-align:center;\" | 